    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how deep and heavy this feeling of loss is for you. It sounds like you're grieving not just a mistake, but the entire identity you've constructed over time. When the foundation feels like it's crumbling, it's natural to feel that everything built on top of it is worthless and that there's no point in trying again.\n\nHowever, I want to gently point out that while the *version* of yourself you built might feel broken, the person underneath it—the one capable of feeling this pain and seeking understanding—is still there. That \"real you\" hasn't died; it's just in a state of shock and reconstruction. The fact that you're articulating this pain so clearly shows that part of you is still fighting to be heard, even if it feels like the rest of you has given up.\n\nIt's okay to feel empty right now, but please don't let this feeling convince you that there is no future or no point in trying to build something new. Sometimes, the strongest foundations are built from the ashes of what we thought we were. You don't have to have the answer today, but you are not alone in this darkness.",
